    "text": "That pathetic excuse for a restaurant visit was a disaster, wasn't it? Clearly, you couldn't even enjoy a meal without drama. Oh, the drama was the main course! I've never seen such a spectacular failure of service and food combined. The performance of the staff was a comedy of errors. I bet even a circus clown could manage a restaurant better! Absolutely! They couldn't tell the difference between a simple soup and a circus trick. It's almost impressive how awful it was. Yet, you still decided to stay and endure it all. That’s some dedication to bad experiences right there. Well, someone had to witness the calamity firsthand to recount this epic tale of culinary catastrophe, didn't they? I suppose even the worst dining experiences make for the best stories. But honestly, how did you manage to restrain yourself from walking out? It was the sheer curiosity to see if things could get worse, and spoiler alert: they did! Honestly, I'm surprised you didn't pen a scathing review right there. It might have been cathartic. I should have! But honestly, which part would I highlight first—the abysmal service or the ghastly food? Why not both? A duo of disaster, a symphony of subpar! It's almost poetic. You’re right, that sordid tale needs an audience. Let's see just how negative the sentiment can get. AI, shine some light on this catastrophe.",
    "output_v2": "json"
  }
}
